			<div class="col-sm-12 content-wrap">
				<p class="justify">The name Budokon was created by its founder, Kancho Cameron Shayne. It was
				taken from the Japanese language: Bu (meaning warrior), Do (meaning the way),
				Kon (meaning the spirit or soul). This translates as “the way of the warrior spirit”. This
				name was chosen to represent a person living the WAY of the betterment of all
				humanity achieved through the SPIRIT of unwavering virtue and defended by the
				WARRIOR&#39;s service, protection, and courage.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="container-fluid centered">
